Itis observable that in continental hagiology Columba is a fe- male appellation; whereas, among the Irish, with one or two trifling exceptions, it belongs to the opposite sex. We have in Adamnan various Latin forms of the name, as Columba, Columbanus, Columbus, and Columb. The first bishop of Dunkeld was Columba, who flourished about 640.
